o the `metrics` parameter to ensure it contains only valid characters (e.g., `[a-zA-Z0-9_,]`) before making the API call.\n\n## Observations (non-blocking)\n- **(Observation)** (`ingest/youtube_client.py:20`) The docstring for `YouTubeClient` claims that \"Error messages redact the header Authorization value if present,\" but there is no visible application code that performs this redaction. While the `googleapiclient` library likely handles this correctly, the docstring makes a claim that is not implemented or verified within this codebase. Suggest removing the claim unless it can be demonstrated to be enforced by the application's own code.\n\n## Summary\nThe review identified one high-severity issue regarding incomplete testing, one medium-severity issue with the robustness of the `.env` parser, and one low-severity issue about missing input validation. The security and OAuth flow implementation appear solid, with correct file permissions and parameter usage. Retry logic is also well-implemented and tested. The main action item is to add cassette-based tests to ensure the `YouTubeClient` works as expected with the provided API response fixtures.\n```",
